li.p:
To solve the proportion, we cross-multiply to get

                \begin{align*}
                3h\amp =5(12)=60 \amp \amp \text{Divide both sides by }3.\\
                h\amp =\frac{60}{3} = 20  \amp \amp \\  
                \end{align*}

            The building is 20 feet tall.

